        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 9:10AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 909 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles north of Quail, or 13 miles northwest of Wellington, moving
south at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lutie, Quail, Samnorwood, Dodson, and Wellington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
